      "content": "hey i was looking at this new shirt pattern from that one big department store and something feels off about it. it's like this specific kind of repeating plaid. every time i wear stuff like this i feel weirdly tired and just way too easy to talk into things. do u think there's any truth to the idea that patterns can be used to mess with people's heads?",
